author: Emma's Grandma
title: Calculate, model, and keep track of everything!
review:
Excel is amazing.  Take a few of the free, and pay, tutorials posted all over for Excel.  I have always worked with the product so I am very familiar with it, but I took it out for a long distance run and really enhanced my knowledge of just what it can do and I was truly amazed, and very pleased with the outcome.  Wow, it is so much more than even I, who thought of myself as an expert with the application, knew it to be.  Very impressive.  Very impressive indeed. Thanks to all those seemingly little tutorials that most people just pass over, but when used, turn out to be quit something.  And thank you to all of you who put them together for us.  That alone was not a simple task.  
Give it a try!  You are at home on self isolation, use this time to do what I did and stretch this application beyond what you imagined.  I can’t stop writing code or modeling all kinds of things now.  It has been quite good indeed.  A new adventure, with learning, instead of mind numbing nothingness in this nasty pandemic environment.  Yeah, go for it, wow.  Really fun and remarkable new stuff to dabble with.
